</h3>
<p>
    A <strong>light or ultralight spinning rod (6–7 feet)</strong> paired with a smooth reel spooled with <strong>4–8 lb test line</strong> is perfect for rainbow trout. If you prefer fly fishing, a <strong>5-weight rod</strong> with floating line and a 9-foot leader works well in Oregon’s streams and lakes.
</p>
<p>
    Don’t forget to bring polarized sunglasses—they help you see underwater structure and spot feeding trout more easily. A small net, tackle box, and portable chair can make your trip far more enjoyable.
</p>
