<h2>
    Fishing Regulations and Licensing Requirements
</h2>
<p>
    Before heading out, ensure you’re following the <strong>Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife (ODFW)</strong> regulations. Here’s what you need to know:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Fishing License:</strong> Anyone aged 12 and older must have a valid Oregon fishing license.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Daily Bag Limit:</strong> Typically, 5 trout per day — but always verify as it varies by location.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Size Limits:</strong> Some waters have catch-and-release-only or size restrictions.
