<h2>
    Tips and Techniques for Catching Rainbow Trout
</h2>
<h3>
    Fly Fishing Techniques
</h3>
<p>
    Fly fishing for rainbow trout in Oregon is both art and science. Focus on <strong>natural presentation</strong> — trout are keenly aware of movement and shadows. Use small nymphs during the day and dry flies during evening hatches. Casting upstream and letting your fly drift naturally with the current often yields the best results.
</p>
<h3>
    Spin Casting Tips
</h3>
<p>
    For spin anglers, <strong>slow retrieves</strong> and <strong>light tackle</strong> are key. Cast near drop-offs, submerged logs, or inlets where trout feed. Use <strong>inline spinners</strong> or <strong>small spoons</strong> in silver or gold tones — these mimic baitfish perfectly. Change up your retrieve speed if fish aren’t biting.
</p>
