</p>
<p>
    <strong>2. What’s the best month to catch rainbow trout near Salem?</strong><br>
    April through June and September through October are peak months due to ideal water temperatures and stocking schedules.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>3. What bait works best for stocked trout?</strong><br>
    PowerBait in bright colors like chartreuse or rainbow glitter is highly effective in stocked lakes and ponds.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>4. Are there any catch-and-release-only waters near Salem?</strong><br>
    Yes. Certain stretches of the North Santiam River and parts of Marion Lake are catch-and-release only. Always check local regulations.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>5. Can I fish year-round for rainbow trout in Oregon?</strong><br>
    Many lakes and reservoirs remain open year-round, but some rivers have seasonal closures to protect spawning fish.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>6. What’s the limit for rainbow trout per day?</strong><br>
